<HEADLINE> New US Ambassador Presents Credentials to French </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The new United States
Ambassador to France Felix Rohatyn today presented the letter of
credentials to President Jacques Chirac, said the Elysee
presidential palace.
</P>
<P>
A 68-year-old New Yorker banker and a close associate of U.S.
President Bill Clinton, Rohatyn replaced Madam Pamela Harriman,
the well-known British-American diplomat who died on February 5 in
Paris.
</P>
<P>
A fluent speaker of French, Rohatyn spent part of his childhood
in France until his family was driven away by Nazi occupiers.
</P>
</TEXT>
