<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Doohan Wants to Break Agostini's Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Australian Michael Doohan, who
has won a fourth consecutive 500cc world title, wants to beat a
25-year-old record in Sunday's Catalunya Grand Prix.
</P>
<P>
So far this season Doohan has equalled Italian Giacomo
Agostini's 1972 feat of 11 wins.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, he will either break it or suffer his worst result
of the season -- no great drama since he has finished first in
every race bar one second place.
</P>
<P>
Strangely, Doohan has never won at the Barcelona circuit
although he did clinch his third world title there last season
with a second place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
