<HEADLINE> World Cup Ticket Prices Set </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Prices for next year's World
Cup final at the 80,000-seat Stade de France have been decided,
organizers said here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ticket prices will be in four categories -- 350 Francs (58
U.S. dollars), 950 Francs (158 U.S. dollars), 1,750 Francs (290
U.S. dollars), 2,950 Francs (U.S. 490 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Prices for the semi-finals will range from 300 Francs (50
U.S. dollars) to 1,850 Francs (308 U.S. dollars). Fans will have
to pay between 250 Francs (40 U.S. dollars) and 750 Francs (125
U.S. dollars) for quarter-final matches.
</P>
<P>
Ticket prices for champions Brazil's opening match on June 10
will range from 200 Francs (33 U.S. dollars) to 1,250 Francs (208
U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
