<DOCNO> XIE19970912.0010 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-11 16:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian Minister Rejects EU Claim on Pistachios </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Agricultural Minister
Issa Kalantari today rejected European Union's (EU) claim on
Iranian pistachios, saying that the pistachios is exported to
Europe after thorough examination.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural minister said "Iranian pistachios exported to
Europe gets permission for distribution and consumption after
receiving standard license and undergoing thorough examinations
in Europe," the official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on a temporary ban imposed by the European Union
Commission on import of Iranian pistachios, Kalantari said that
last year 5,000 containers of pistachios weighing 90,000 tonnes
arrived in the European market, one of which was contaminated
for various reasons.
</P>
<P>
The EU said Tuesday that it had banned imports of pistachios
from Iran because of fears of contamination by aflatoxin b1, a
carcinogenic substance produced by molds.
</P>
<P>
Kalantari said EU officials take 240 kilograms of pistachios
out of each 20-tonne pistachio container for quality control and
sampling tests before they issue clearance permit for their
export.
</P>
<P>
He said that Iran's exported pistachios are systematically
dried within 16 hours of their harvest in order to keep them
free from any toxin.
</P>
<P>
Kalantari said that in October an EU delegation comprising
health care, quality control and laboratory experts would arrive
in Iran to inspect production, harvest, testing and export of
Iranian pistachios.
</P>
<P>
Kalantari said that 400,000 hectares of lands in Iran are
under cultivation of pistachios and that Iran's pistachio
production is expected to double to 400,000 tonnes a year in the
next five years.
</P>
<P>
He said that each tonne of Iranian pistachios is now sold for
about 5,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Iran earned nearly 400 million dollars from export of 130,000
tonnes of pistachios last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
