<HEADLINE> Khamenei: Loyalty, Cooperation Needed in Armed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Supreme Leader Ali
Khamenei today stressed the need of loyalty and cooperation in the
country's armed forces.
</P>
<P>
"The country needs army men who are devout, effective,
committed and equipped with advanced resources," he said in a
ceremony to promote the military rank of Islamic Revolution Guards
Corps' (IRGC) new commander Seyed-Yahya Rahim Safavi to major
general.
</P>
<P>
Tehran Radio quoted Khamenei as stressing the importance of the
close cooperation between the IRGC and the army to bring the ranks
up to the standards.
</P>
<P>
Military observers here said the Iranian army is regarded as
less ideological, and more hierarchical than the IRGC.
</P>
<P>
Iran's army, especially its senior commanders were mainly
trained by the Americans, but the IRGC and the commanders obtained
combat effectiveness and became an important military force of
Iran through fightings against the Iraqis from 1980 to 1988.
</P>
<P>
Praising the loyalty of the IRGC, Khamenei said it was only
after the (Iran-Iraq) war that the IRGC got the chance to
reorganize and accord ranks to its fighters who had been too busy
fighting to think about their military ranks.
</P>
<P>
General Safavi, a former Brigadier General, was appointed by
Khamenei as IRGC commander Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
