<DOCNO> XIE19970912.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-11 16:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Parliamentarian Conference Opens in Cairo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The 98th Inter-Parliamentary
Union (IPU) Conference opened here today, highlighting the topics
of democracy and employment.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,600 parliamentarians from 138 member states
together with representatives of 20 international organizations
take part in the biannual conference which will last till
September 16.
</P>
<P>
The two main topics for discussion at the conference this year
are "ensuring lasting democracy by forging close links between
parliament and the people" and "employment in a globalizing
world."
</P>
<P>
In parallel to these debates, IPU's governing bodies will
consider a Declaration on Democracy, prepared over the last year
by the IPU and international experts.
</P>
<P>
Sub-committees will discuss issues including the human rights
of parliamentarians, security and cooperation in the
Mediterranean, the situation in Cyprus, Middle East peace and
International Humanitarian Law.
</P>
<P>
In a message addressed to the inauguration, U.N. Secretary
General Kofi Annan stressed that he attaches importance to
building close ties between the IPU and the U.N..
</P>
<P>
Annan's massage was delivered on his behalf by
U.N. Undersecretary General and Director General of the
U.N. Office at Geneva Vladimir Petrovsky.
</P>
<P>
A few cooperation agreements between the IPU and
U.N. organizations last year marked a beginning of the
IPU-U.N. cooperation, he noted.
</P>
<P>
This cooperation "reflects a most welcome and promising
development: the emergence of new actors on the world stage, and
their growing influence in shaping the international agenda,"
Annan added.
</P>
<P>
Annan said that the IPU agenda, as usual, includes some of the
urgent concerns of the present day, which coincide with U.N.'s
endeavors around the globe.
</P>
<P>
IPU Secretary General Pierre Corino, in a report delivered at
the conference, said the IPU has been edging closer to the
U.N. and is studying an agreement to make it a U.N. executive
agency.
</P>
<P>
He said the IPU's plan to open an office at the U.N. would be a
fundamental step crowning the union's efforts to consolidate its
relationship with the U.N..
</P>
<P>
The 138-member IPU was formed in 1889 to promote personal
contact of MPs to the end of developing democratic representation
and promoting cooperation between the institutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
