<DOCNO> XIE19970912.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Vigorously Explore Hydropower Resources of Yangtze River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The China Yangtze River Three
Gorges Project Development Corporation has been making preliminary
preparations for two big hydropower stations on the upper
reaches of the Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
Early feasibility designs for construction of Xiangjiaba and
Xiluodu hydropower stations have passed appraisal, and the
corporation will oversee construction while watching over its
building of the Three Gorges Project.
</P>
<P>
The Xiluodu hydropower station will have a combined generating
capacity of 14.4 million kw and will take 14 years to complete.
It will become China's second largest after the Three Gorges Dam.
</P>
<P>
Xiajiaba hydropower station will have a generating capacity of
six million kw and will be able to generate 30.4 billion kwh
of electricity a year.
</P>
<P>
Experts say the construction of the two hydropower stations
will greatly improve China's energy structure, alleviate power
shortages in east China, improve navigation conditions on the
Yangtze during the dry season and advance economic development of
southwest China.
</P>
<P>
Construction will start on one of the two projects in 2005.
</P>
<P>
The hydropower resources of the Yangtze is
estimated at 200 million kw, accounting for more than half of the
country's total, most of which are discovered on the upper
and middle reaches of the Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
To fully explore the rich hydropower resources on the Yangtze,
China has planned to construct 20 tiered hydropower stations, with
Gezhouba hydropower station as the first, followed by the Three
Gorges Dam now under construction at the middle reaches of the
Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
The Gezhouba station is now capable of generating 14.09 billion
kwh of electricity a year, while the Three Gorges Dam will have an
aggregate installed capacity of 18.2 million kw and will be able
to generate 84.7 billion kwh of electricity annually.
</P>
<P>
Four hydropower stations including the two at Xiangjiaba and
Xiluodu, can be built on the Jinshan River, the upper section of
the Yangtze. The Jingsha River has a natural drop of 3,280 m and
a theoretical hydropower reserve of 55.37 million kw.
</P>
<P>
Generators with a combined generating capacity of 30.7 million
kw to 43.1 million kw will be installed at the four hydropower
stations which will be able to generate 156.9 billion to 184.4
billion kwh of electricity a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
