<HEADLINE> Leading Business School to Open Branch in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 11 (Xinhua) -- A leading North American
business school announced here today that it will build an
education center in Hong Kong for executive development and MBA
programs.
</P>
<P>
The University of Western Ontario's Richard Ivey School of
Business will locate its Ivey Business School/Asia in the
newly-built Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center, and plans
to open its first executive MBA class in September 1998, which
will be taught by senior Ivey faculty.
</P>
<P>
The new school will enroll students from Hong Kong, China's
interior areas and other parts of Asia. With part-time courses
during two week-day evenings and Saturdays, students will receive
an MBA degree from the University of Western Ontario.
</P>
<P>
Ivey School of Business has MBA exchange programs with China's
Qinghua University and Fudan University.  
