<HEADLINE> Youth Given 10 Years in Jail for Marseille Murder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 11 (Xinhua) -- A 16-year-old youth was
sentenced to 10 years in prison by a Marseille court for murdering
a 14-year-old boy, Nicolas Bourgat, in the southern French
metropolis one year ago to a day, reported Agence France-Presse.
</P>
<P>
The murder caused a sensation in France because the murderer
was reportedly a North African immigrant who said that he killed
Nicolas Bourgat simply because he felt inferior to him.
</P>
<P>
The far-right National Front (FN) party of Jean-Marie Le Pen
took advantage of the murder to fan racist prejudice against
immigrants, and organized a huge protest in Marseille last
September.
</P>
<P>
The accused young man, whose name was not published by the
court, admitted being guilty of willing manslaughter by stabbing
to death Nicolas with a knife, when the latter was eating a
sandwich with his friends in downtown Marseille.
</P>
<P>
The French law allows a court to give a maximum sentence of 16
years in jail for a crime like this committed by a minor of 16.
</P>
<P>
The father of Nicolas, Michel Bourgat, said after the verdict
that this sentence had not relieved him of his pain caused by the
death of his son. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
