<HEADLINE> CPPCC Members Inspect Prosperous Town in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 11 (Xinhua) -- A group of members of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) today
inspected Baigou, a north China town renowned for its business
savvy.
</P>
<P>
Located 100 km south of Beijing, Baigou was once famous for
selling inexpensive, but well-made goods. However, the town lost
its reputation years ago when defective goods and
pirated items infiltrated the market.
</P>
<P>
To revive its image, the local government has worked out a
series of regulations to return its markets to their glory days.
</P>
<P>
During today's inspection, CPPCC members expressed their
satisfactions for the tidy streets and orderly marketplaces, and
gave high marks to the local government for the overall
improvement of residents' quaility of life.
</P>
<P>
"Fake goods or low-quality items have been wiped out of our
markets through two years of hard work," said the town head,
adding they are trying to build Baigou into a shopping center,
as well as a new tourist destination.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the sales volume in the town hit four billion yuan,
with more than 80,000 visitors coming and going per day, and the
per capita monthly income exceeded 3,600 yuan.
</P>
<P>
CPPCC inspectors offered some suggestions for the town's future
development, and promised to promote Baigou to more investors both
at home and abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
