 two main tasks for his department: to explain the position of the
 Chinese Government on foreign affairs related to the Hong Kong
SAR and major international matters, and to handle applications
of resident or temporary foreign reporters in HKSAR for coverage
in China's interior areas.
</P>
<P>
The Basic Law stipulates that HKSAR residents enjoy freedom of
the press and publication, the spokesman said, noting that two
months' facts after the return of Hong Kong showed that it was
unnecessary for some people to worry about the matter.
</P>
<P>
He stated that the office would not intervene in proper and
lawful news coverage by both the HKSAR and foreign reporters.
</P>
<P>
Present at the reception were Commissioner of the Chinese
Foreign Ministry in Hong Kong SAR Ma Yuzhen and his deputies Zhao
Jihua and Liu Hongxiao. 
