<HEADLINE> UK Interest Rates Remain Unchanged at 7 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Britain's central bank the
Bank of England announced today that interest rates are to stay at
7 percent for the time being.
</P>
<P>
After two days of its monthly monetary meeting, the bank
decided to leave interest rates unchanged, the first time it has
decided against a rate rise since it was given the power to set
them after the May 1 general election.
</P>
<P>
The move had been widely expected by economists who believe
that the country's economic growth is slowing down. The central
bank also indicated last month that after four rate rises in a row
in as many months it would pause for thought before moving again.
</P>
<P>
The bank's decision was vindicated by recent economic figures
showing that Britain's economic recovery is starting to ease,
which means that inflation fears are lessened. 
</P>
</TEXT>
