<HEADLINE> Nigerian Leader Physically Fit: Diplomat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's High Commissioner
to Zimbabwe Lamine Metteden has dismissed the reported serious
illness of Nigerian military ruler Sani Abacha as pure
speculation by the western press, saing Abacha is physically fit
and going about state business normally.
</P>
<P>
General Abacha (53), who has ruled Africa's most populous
nation of over 100 million people since taking power in a
military coup in 1993, was this week reported by two major
international news agencies as being ''very ill'' with cirrhosis
of the liver.
</P>
<P>
Quoting a privately-owned weekly, the agencies said Abacha's
health had seriously deteriorated in recent months and the man
has been suffering from liver problems for about 10 years.
</P>
<P>
Metteden said here today the report that Abacha was seriously
sick could not be true.
</P>
<P>
