<HEADLINE> 7 Iranian Workers Kidnapped in Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Iran announced here today
that its seven aid workers were kidnapped by an Afghan group in
northern Afghanistan Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Ministry said in a statement that Iran called for
an immediate release of the aid workers. The statement said that
the Afghan group is responsible for the safety of the captives.
</P>
<P>
Two of the relief workers were extending humanitarian
services to the Afghan refugees and the other five were working
in a clinic in the suburb of Mazar-i-Sharif in northern
Afghanistan when they were kidnapped.
</P>
<P>
The statement condemned kidnapping of the workers who were
serving to relieve the sufferings of the Muslim people in
Afghanistan on humanitarian ground. 
