<HEADLINE> S. Leone Junta Bans Chiefs From Importing Water </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The military junta in Sierra
Leone has ordered chiefs in the diamond region of Kono not to
drink imported mineral water until they fix local water works
used by the rest of the people there.
</P>
<P>
While paramount chiefs resort to drinking imported mineral
water, poor subjects drink from dirty and contaminated pools,
exposing them to all types of illness and disease," said Corporal
Tamba Gborie.
</P>
<P>
The chiefs are "selfish and greedy", said Gborie, who led a
section of junior officers and soldiers in the coup on May 25
that overthrew the country's legitimate government of President
Ahemd Tejan Kabbah.
</P>
<P>
"Now to pay for your wrong-doing and to bring instant equality
between the poor and the rich, I am putting a ban on the sale of
mineral water in Kono," he declared, quoted by a report reaching
here today.
</P>
<P>
Gborie also said electricity generators would be ordered
switched off in a month so as to encourage the renovation of a
local power plant.
</P>
<P>
The report did not say when Gborie ordered the ban, and his
position in the military government remains unknown.
</P>
<P>
Gborie's voice was first heard over the radio on the day of
the coup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
