<HEADLINE> Kohl Upbeat About German Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FRANKFURT, September 11 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Helmut
Kohl today expressed optimism about Germany's economic outlook,
predicting that the country's gross domestic product (GDP) would
grow by nearly 3 percent next year.
</P>
<P>
In a speech at the opening ceremony of the Frankfurt
international car show today, Kohl criticized the widespread
scepticism among the German public about the economy, saying that
although the current growth was mainly driven by exports, there
was reason for Germans to be optimistic instead of just
complaining about the weak domestic growth.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed confidence that the export boom would also
stimulate a revival of domestic business in many sectors.
</P>
<P>
Kohl made the remarks after the German Federal Statistics
Office said Wednesday that the German economy was accelerating by
growing 2.9 percent in the second quarter and 2.0 percent in the
first six months of this year. 
</P>
