<HEADLINE> European Shares Down on Weak Wall Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Major stock markets in Europe
all ended today sharply down, undermined by a softer dollar and
Wall Street's continuing decline.
</P>
<P>
London's FTSE 100 index remained sharply lower as the Dow
followed on from Wednesday's weakness and ended 50.4 points down
at 4,854.8.
</P>
<P>
As expected the Bank of England left base interest rates
unchanged at 7 percent following its latest monetary committee
meeting.
</P>
<P>
A raft of first-half results from several leading FTSE 100
stocks provided the other main focus of news.
</P>
<P>
German shares in Frankfurt ended 1.9 percent lower, hurt by
overnight Wall Street losses and a softer dollar. The DAX-30 index
fell by 77.59 points below the 4,000-point level to stand at
3,972.55 by the close of the session.
</P>
<P>
On the Paris bourse, shares also closed lower, with fresh
selling on Wall Street and the dollar's weaker tone continuing to
weigh on the market. The CAC-40 index finished down 30.97 points
at 2,843.6. 
</P>
