<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 11 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister Hubert
Vedrine today launched what was the strongest attack ever made by
the French government against the policy of the Israeli government
under Prime Minister Benyamin Netanyahu toward the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
"This is a catastrophic policy, in the present and for the
future, for the Palestinians, for Israel and for the whole
region," said Vedrine in a speech at a conference of the Socialist
Party held in Montpellier, southern France.
</P>
<P>
He said that the policy of Netanyahu has forced the
Palestinians to "the level of exasperation and despair without
precedent."
</P>
<P>
