no more perspective," said Vedrine while trying to contain his
anger.
</P>
<P>
The attack by the French foreign minister was launched when
United States Secretary of State Madeleine Albright is on a peace
mission in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse said that today's attack by Vedrine, who
was the secretary general of President Francois Mitterrand, was
unusual because the French Socialists are traditionally more
sympathetic with Israel than the French rightwing parties.
</P>
<P>
When President Jacques Chirac visited Jerusalem last October,
he clashed with Israeli security agents who tried to separate him
from Palestinians who came to welcome him. 
