your citizens, I assure you of the most profound sympathy from
myself and the French people," said Chirac in the message sent to
Rene, which was published by the Elysee presidential palace.
</P>
<P>
Chirac also asked Rene to convey the condolences to the
families of the victims.
</P>
<P>
Eighty-one people were drowned and many disappeared in the
sinking of the Fierte Govanienne ferry when it was entering the
port of Montrouis Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
