in Yaounde on September 10, according to Radio Cameroun today.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was aimed at bringing together experts in
universities, the world bank and other non-governmental
organizations to examine the economic problems and propose
solutions that could help eliminate poverty in the country.
</P>
<P>
