Annan hoped that in the final discussions of the U.S. congress,
some of the conditions could be dropped and the problem could be
worked out so that the work of the United Nations would not be
disrupted and the tension among the member states would not be
increased.
</P>
<P>
The secretary-general stressed that the United Nations would
continue to go ahead with reforms and work on priorities to face
the 21 century. 
