<HEADLINE> Executives of Large State Firms Optimistic About Prospect </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Executives of five state
large groups in China today said that exploration for effective
forms to materialize public ownership for developing productive
forces and promote the shareholding system will be one of the new
breakthroughs in the reform of the country's state businesses.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Kuangyu, chairman of the board of directors of Shanghai
Textile Holdings Group, said that people used to think the state
and collective sectors were the only forms to materialize public
ownership.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin, however, broadened the concept of public ownership
by including the state and collective sectors of the mixed
ownership of the economy in his report he delivered at the opening
session of the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of
China, which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhu, nine of the 240 joint ventures in Shanghai's
textile industry have introduced the shareholding system.
</P>
<P>
"I used to think that once an enterprise drawns in overseas
fund and is listed on the stock market, it is no longer of public
ownership," said Zhu. "Jiang's report today has strengthened my
confidence in the prospect of state businesses," he added.
</P>
<P>
Zhu, together with executives of four other influential
companies in China, were invited to give a press conference this
afternoon on the hot topic of reforms in state enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Geng Zhaojie, general manager of the China First Automobile
Works, said the shareholding system has enabled his group
to operate more effectively.
</P>
<P>
Through fund-raising, this largest automobile producer of China
now has a total of 2.8 billion yuan at its own disposal as against
750 million yuan before, increasing the value of its state assets.
</P>
<P>
"The shareholding system does mot have any impact on the nature
of the public ownership of the works because the works controls
majority of the stocks of its three listed affiliations, which has
introduced a shareholding system," he said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the worker's security and unemployment following
the introduction of the shareholding system, Liu Jie, chairman and
president of the Anshan Iron and Steel Group, told the reporters
that China is introducing a social old-age system. A steel
rolling mill of the Group, which was set up not long ago, has
decided to take out some money from its annual profits, which is
equivalent to 10 percent of its total payroll, for the medical
security fund.
</P>
<P>
In response to the role of Party organizations in shareholding
enterprises, Wang Guoxing, vice-president of the Handan Iron and
Steel Corporation Ltd, said that the major role of the grass-roots
Party organizations is to help the business executives to mobilize
the enthusiasm of the workers and improve the business management.
</P>
<P>
The ideas of the Party organizations will only become policy
decisions through legal procedures and the company law.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, introducing the shareholding system and the
bringing into full play the role of the Party organizations are
not contradictary," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
