<HEADLINE> Yeltsin, Ramos Agree on More Cooperation in Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris
Yeltsin held talks here today with visiting Philippines
President Fidel Ramos.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders exchanged views on a wide range of issues in
the political, economic, cultural and military technology fields
and pledged to enhance cooperation in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, they signed a joint declaration on
cooperation, the official Russian Itar-Tass news agency said.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference after the signing ceremony, Yeltsin said,
"Russia should not fix its eyes on Europe and the West only, but
also need to develop relations with Asian countries."
</P>
<P>
The Asian-Pacific region is "extremely important" to Russia not
only because two thirds of the Russian territory is in Asia but
also because Russia hopes to engage itself more in Asian-Pacific
affairs, including those of the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN), Yeltsin said.
</P>
<P>
He said that he and Ramos held identical views on all bilateral
and international issues which they discussed in their talks.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said that it is very important for the Philippines to
develop relations with Russia in economy, technology and regional
security.
</P>
<P>
This is because a large portion of the Russian territory is in
Asia and the Russian economy is growing, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said Russia's role is important in a new multi-polar
world which has no place for any dominating power.
</P>
<P>
A new world should be based on uniform equality among all
countries, Ramos added.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers of the two countries also signed two
inter-governmental agreements on cooperation today.
</P>
<P>
Ramos arrived here on September 11 for a two-day official visit
to Russia, the first by a head of an ASEAN member country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
