<HEADLINE> Chinese Focusing Attention On CPC National Congress (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The 15th National Congress of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) which opened today in Beijing's
Great Hall of the People has become the focus of the Chinese
people's attention and a festival atmosphere has pervaded the
nation's capital.
</P>
<P>
Tian'anmen Square at the heart of the city has been turned into
a garden overflowing with flowers. A large fountain at the
square's center spurts 15 columns of water into the sky. Two huge
lighted billboards proclaiming "Celebrating 15th CPC National
Congress" and "Celebrating 48th National Day," stand just north
of the Monument to the People's Heroes.
</P>
<P>
As the clock struck nine this morning, more than 100
televisions in the downtown Xidan Department Store aired the live
telecast of the congress's opening ceremony, bringing in a flood
of customers.
</P>
<P>
In his home near the Great Hall, the 85-year-old An Dewang was
listening to Jiang Zemin's opening speech on the radio.
</P>
<P>
"I've experienced the bulk of the three historical changes
taking place within the century," said An, who belongs to the Hui
ethnic group.
</P>
<P>
"The changes are great, and my sons and grandsons are living in
a good time," he noted, adding that he believes the life will
continue to improve.
</P>
<P>
Huang Maozhou, manager of a lamp and lantern store near the
square, was gazing fixedly at the TV screen while at the same time
answering phones.
</P>
<P>
"Nowadays in China, you must be aware of the government
policies if you want to do business," said Huang, who hoped that
the Party will work harder still to fight corruption and improve
the legal system.
</P>
<P>
"Business would flourish only when the market activities are
standardized," he said, whose business has expanded rapidly over
the past three years.
</P>
</TEXT>
