<HEADLINE> Chinese Focusing Attention on CPC National Congress (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the waiting room at Beijing Railway Station, travelers were
flocked around more than 30 Television sets to watch the opening
of the congress.
</P>
<P>
"What the folks from the northeast care most about is whether
the congress can help the state-owned enterprises to make
profits," said He Shoucai, who lives in the old industrial base of
Shenyang. He came to the station four hours ahead of his departure
time just to watch the telecast of the congress.
</P>
<P>
At 10 a.m., a stock trading agency in the East District was
crowded with stock investors heatedly discussing the reform of the
stock system as referred to today by Jiang Zemin in his work
report.
</P>
<P>
"I think that the shares issued by the state-owned enterprises
are promising," said Liu Wei. Calling himself "a professional
stock investor," Liu believed that these factories will be
extricated from their difficulties after the congress.
</P>
<P>
Wang Xiaolin, a taxi driver, listened to the broadcast while
on the road.
</P>
<P>
"Many of the customers have discussed the Party Congress with
me recently. They care about it," he said, hoping that the policy
of reform and opening-up will remain unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Wang bought a car and joined the taxi business several years
ago when he was laid off. Now he earns 5,000 yuan (600 US dollars)
a month.
</P>
<P>
Yi Baoyun, deputy-director of the Marxism Institute of Beijing
University, expressed his satisfaction with Jiang's report. He said
that "Jiang has called on the country to hold high the great banner
of Deng Xiaoping Theory, and carry forward in an all-round way the
great cause of building socialism with Chinese characteristics to
the 21st century."
</P>
<P>
This fully shows that the third generation of leaders with
Jiang Zemin at the core has the spirit to carry forward the cause
and forge ahead into the future, he said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Yin said, "after hearing the report, I feel very
encouraged, and am confident in my country's revitalization in the
next century."  
