<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK, Romania Traders Sign Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 12 (Xinhua) -- A cooperation agreement
between the Chinese Manufacturers' Association (CMA) of Hong Kong
and the Chamber of Commerce and Industry of Romania and Bucharest
Municipality (CCIR) was signed here today.
</P>
<P>
The signing ceremony was officiated by Emil Constantinescu,
president of Romania. On behalf of the two sides, Herbert Liang,
president of CMA, and George Cojocaru, president of the CCIR,
signed the agreement.
</P>
<P>
Herbert Liang said that with forward-looking governments and
dynamic business sectors, Romania and Hong Kong offer foreign
investors and enterprises a flourishing business environment where
they can find plentiful business opportunities.
</P>
<P>
He said that he believes the normalization of working
relationships between the two organizations will foster stronger
economic ties and cooperation, especially for the business
communities, between Hong Kong and Romania.
</P>
<P>
CCIR President George Cojocaru stressed that the new Romania
government is committed to attracting more foreign investment,
adding that it is time for Hong Kong traders and manufacturers to
explore the favorable opportunities in Romania.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, both parties will render one
another valuable cooperation, join their efforts to the benefit of
the general interests of both Hong Kong and Romanian industries,
further strengthen their relations, and promote among their
associates of exchanges of technology, investment and trade.
</P>
