on a Salvadoran arrested in connection with recent bombings of
tourist installations in Havana.
</P>
<P>
The Washington Post:
</P>
<P>
-- A major internal investigation of gender relations in the
U.S. Army has found endemic sexual harassment "crossing gender,
rank, and racial lines" that is undermining the integration of
women in the largest branch of the armed forces.
</P>
<P>
-- Russia delivered a harsh warning to NATO against putting
pressure on the Bosnian Serbs, declaring that any attack against a
radio and television station controlled by the Serbs would be an
intolerable use of force that could imperil the peacekeeping
mission.
</P>
<P>
The Wall Street Journal
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President and General Secretary of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Jiang Zemin opened a CPC congress with a
speech backing political and legal reforms, saying the drive for a
market economy may go on for a century.
</P>
<P>
-- Asian Americans asked for a federal civil rights
investigation, saying they are being made scapegoats in the
campaign fund-raising affair. 
