<HEADLINE> Tibetans Hail Opening of Party Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Atop the golden roof of the
Potala Palace, the most sacred temple of Tibetan Buddhism, flutter
the national flag and banners proclaiming "Warm Celebration of the
victorious opening of the 15th National Congress of Communist
Party of China (CPC)."
</P>
<P>
Local residents in Lhasa, capital of the Tibet Autonomous
Region are celebrating the opening of the 15th CPC Congress today.
</P>
<P>
Inside the Johkang Monastery, lamas are reciting scriptures
eulogizing the big event. One of them told a Xinhua reporter that
they had been praying for the opening of the Party Congress for
the past few days, wishing for the strong leadership of the
Chinese Communist Party, which can bring about further improvement
for the Tibetans' lives.
</P>
<P>
At about 9 a.m., people stopped on the streets around the
temple to watch the live broadcast of the opening of the Party
Congress.
</P>
<P>
A herdswoman from northern Tibet said that remarkable changes
have taken place at her hometown. The Communist Party and the
government have helped them to settle down, and her family are
working hard to lead a good life. She expressed the hope that the
Congress would set more beneficial policies to help them.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of residents living around the Bargor Street in downtown
Lhasa city, gathered at the community committee building to watch
the TV show. Losang Cering, a veteran Party member, came before
8:30 a.m. to get a good seat.
</P>
<P>
"I'm very excited today," he said. "Every Party Congress held
that since the reform and opening up drive in the late 1970s has
brought great changes to our country, the opening the 15th Party
Congress will surely bring us a rosier future."
</P>
<P>
While most people were watching the event on TV, workers at the
Lhasa Beer Factory, the only enterprise experimenting with the
modern managment system in Tibet, were busy working.
</P>
<P>
Basang Zholma, a quality inspector of the factory, said: "It is
the Party's reform policy that has saved our enterprise. We hope
the reform of the state-owned enterprises will be deepened after
the congress."
</P>
<P>
Lhamin Soinam Lhunzhub, vice-chairman of the People's Political
Consultative Conference (PPCC) of the Tibetan Autonomous Region,
said after viewing the opening ceremony of the Party Congress that
the speech made by Jiang Zemin at the opening "is exciting and
inspiring."
</P>
<P>
"I believe more firmly that by holding the great banner of Deng
Xiaoping Theory higher, the Communist Party of China will be able
to lead the Chinese people of all ethnic groups to build China
into a more prosperous and stronger country," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
