<HEADLINE> Turkish President to Visit Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel is to pay a one-day visit to Egypt next Tuesday, the
Turkish Foreign Ministry announced in a written statement today.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that Demirel will exchange views with his
Egyptian counterpart Hosni Mubarak on bilateral, regional and
international issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Observers here said that Turkey's increasingly close military
cooperation with Israel is expected to be discussed by the two
leaders.
</P>
<P>
Recent media reports about the Israeli-Turkish-U.S. joint
naval war games, scheduled for November in the eastern
Mediterranean, triggered strong criticism from Egypt and other
Arab countries.
</P>
<P>
Demirel called off a planned visit to Egypt in May due to
alleged technical reasons. At that time, Turkey was accused by
some Arab nations, including Egypt, of violating Iraq's
sovereignty when launching a massive cross-border military strike
against the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) in northern
Iraq. 
</P>
