<HEADLINE> Mubarak, Albright to Hold Talks in Alexandria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak will meet U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright
Saturday in Alexandria, a port city overlooking the Mediterranean
Sea, Egypt's Middle East News Agency (MENA) reported today.
</P>
<P>
Their talks will deal with all issues relating to the Middle
East peace process, the agency quoted Egyptian Foreign Minister
Amr Moussa as saying.
</P>
<P>
Albright's visit to the region came at a time when violence is
escalating and the Palestinians are suffering from Israeli
intensified pressures, Moussa said.
</P>
<P>
All this called for a U.S. effective intervention and
cooperation among all parties concerned, he added.
</P>
<P>
Albright is expected to hold talks with Moussa to discuss the
ways of reviving the peace process before her meeting with
Mubarak.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian-Israeli peace negotiations came to a halt
since Israel began construction of a controversial Jewish
settlement in Arab East Jerusalem in March.
</P>
<P>
Egypt will be the fourth leg of Albright's Middle East tour
that has taken her to Israel, the Palestinian self-rule areas and
will take her to Syria later today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
