<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Waigel Upbeat About Germany's Meeting Euro Deficit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 12 (Xinhua) -- German Finance Minister Theo
Waigel said today that Germany was in the course of meeting the
budget deficit criteria this year for joining the single European
currency, the euro.
</P>
<P>
"Meeting the Maastricht deficit criteria for 1997 is within
reach," he told parliament. Official data released Wednesday
showed the country's deficit in the first half was 3.1 percent of
the gross domestic product (GDP).
</P>
<P>
Under the Maastricht Treaty, athe European Union countries must
keep their 1997 budget deficit under 3 percent of GDP for taking
part in the January 1, 1999 launch of the euro. 
</P>
</TEXT>
