<HEADLINE> Hongkong Telecom Provides Services for WB/IMF Meetings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Hongkong Telecom has been
appointed as a major telecom services provider to the forthcoming
World Bank/International Monetary Fund Annual Meetings.
</P>
<P>
Over 13,000 representatives from some 180 countries and regions
are going to participate in the event to be held between September
15 and 25 at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center
(HKCEC) Extension.
</P>
<P>
This world-focused event calls for the installation of a
sophisticated communication infrastructure inside the largest
meeting venue in Asia, encompassing a full spectrum of
communication needs throughout the meeting period.
</P>
<P>
To meet the complex requirements, Hongkong Telecom, which is
also a major telecom services provider for the return ceremony,
is building and installing all the voice, data and video networks,
as well as providing a full array of telecom services including
telephones, fax, telex, Internet, IDD, mobile and video links at
the meeting venues.
</P>
<P>
In addition to building over 4,200 voice outlets and 2,600 data
outlets at the HKCEC Extension, Hongkong Telecom is also
installing a large system providing more than 2,000 telephone
extensions for over 900 temporary offices set up for participating
delegates.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting period, two service centers will be set up
by the company, providing one-stop-shop services for meeting
delegates and media representatives respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
