<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Re-exports Volume Up in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The value of Hong Kong's
re-exports increased in July this year by 4.7 percent over a year
earlier to reach 116.4 billion U.S. dollars, according to official
statistics available here today.
</P>
<P>
The statistics issued by the Census and Statistics Department
said that the value of imports rose by 9 percent to 151 billion
U.S. dollars but that of domestic exports decreased by 2.5 percent
to 20.3 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The value of re-exports in the first seven month of this year,
at 691.5 billion U.S. dollars, increased by 4.5 percent over the
same period of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
