<HEADLINE> Party Delegates on Importance of Current Congress (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The 2,000-odd delegates to
the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China talked
about their feelings and expections prior to the congress's
opening session held in the Great Hall of the People in Beijing
today.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Yutai, Party committee secretary of the China Association
for Science and Technology, said the 15th party congress reviewed
the history of China over the past century and look into the
new century.
</P>
<P>
"I expect that current congress will push China's reform
and modernization drive to a new height," he said.
</P>
<P>
Li Youwei, delegate of Guangdong Province and secretary of the
Shenzhen City Party Committee, said, "What we are concerned about
most during the current session is the issue of holding high the
great banner of building socialism with Chinese characteristics."
</P>
<P>
"It is important to emphasize that China is currently in the
primary stage of socialism. All the policies, principles and
the line we adopted have started from this judgment," he added.
</P>
<P>
Under the guidance of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics, Shenzhen recorded a rapid economic development.
Its gross domestic product (GDP) quadrupled in the past five
years, averaging 25 percent a year. It ranks first in the
country in terms of five economic indices. All these
derived from Deng Xiaoping Theory, he said.
</P>
<P>
Liang Guangda, a delegate from the Zhuhai Special Economic Zone
and secretary of the Zhuhai City Party Committee, said that
Zhuhai, as a window of China's economic reform, will continue to
play the role of an experimental ground of reform and opening to
the outside world under the Party line to be set by the 15th
national congress.
</P>
<P>
Another delegate, Wen Shizhen, secretary of the Liaoning
Provincial Party Committee, said that the 15th Party congress is
being held at the turn of the century and the crucial moment of
China's reform and opening up. This is of great significance, he
added.
</P>
<P>
He stressed Liaoning will conscientiously implement the
policies on the reform of the state-owned enterprises,
emancipating the mind and being bold in finding out new ways.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
