<HEADLINE> Party Delegates on Importance of Current Congress (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He Tianfa, vice-chairman of the All-China Federation of
Returned Overseas Chinese, said that he was proud of being a
delegate to the Party congress, which is to work out development
strategy geared to the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Chen Yuan, deputy governor of the People's Bank of China,
expressed the hope that China would be even more prosperous under
the collective leadership of a new Party Central Committee to be
elected by the current congress.
</P>
<P>
Cao Zhenlei, a senior engineer of the China National Council of
Light Industry, said he is concerned about the development
strategy in the field of science and technology contained in the
report delivered by Jiang zemin.
</P>
<P>
Science and technology should play more important role in the
economic restructuing and the change of mode of economic growth,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Lin Liyun, a native of Taiwan, who has been a delegate to the
10th through the 15th Party congress, said the theme of the
current congress is to hold high the great banner of Deong
Xiaoping Theory and advance the cause of building socialism into
the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
She is confident that thanks to the current congress, China
will achieve more successes in economic development and reform.
</P>
<P>
"Our Taiwan compatriots will be encouraged by the rapid growth
on the motherland's mainland and by the sustained prosperity and
stability of Hong Kong since it returned to the motherland," she
said.
</P>
<P>
