<HEADLINE> Hungary Attracts Most Foreign Investment in Central Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Hungary drew 1.22 billion
U.S. dollars of foreign investment in the first half of 1997, an
increase of 70 percent over the same period last year, said the
Ministry of Industry and Commerce and Tourism.
</P>
<P>
By the end of June this year, Hungary had received a
accumulated sum of 17 billion dollars of foreign investment,
continuing to lead in the central European region.
</P>
<P>
Hungary's per capita foreign investment is reportedly to be the
biggest in central Europe, followed closely by the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
Hungary's World Economics Daily said today that the confidence
of foreign investors in Hungary and the favorable conditions for
foreign investment have contributed to the big increase of foreign
investment in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
