<HEADLINE> Bulgarian Defense Minister Addresses Security Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, September 11 (Xinhua) - Some 23,000 million leva (about
12.7 million U.S. dollars) will be needed for Bulgaria's military
in 1998, which will be included in the national defense budget,
Defense Minister Georgi Ananiev said today.
</P>
<P>
At an informal meeting with representatives of the media,
Ananiev asked reporters to write unbiased and objective stories
about national security.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed reporters on the Southeast European defence
ministerial meeting scheduled for October 3 in Sofia, which will
be attended by NATO members and Partnership for Peace countries
from Southeast Europe including Albania, Bulgaria, Slovenia,
Romania, Greece, Turkey, Macedonia, Italy and the United States.
</P>
<P>
The Czech Republic, Poland and Hungary have also been invited
to the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Euro-Atlantic integration and regional cooperation will be
discussed at the meeting, which is expected to provide a chance
for Bulgaria to prove once again that it is a stabilizing factor
in the region.
</P>
<P>
Ananiev said that Bulgaria would propose initiatives useful for
Balkan security. 
</P>
