<HEADLINE> EU Grants 8 Million ECUs For Bosnian Municipal Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The European Union today
announced that it will provide Bosnia with more than 8 million
ECUs to support the country's municipal elections.
</P>
<P>
"Free and fair municipal elections are a vital aspect essential
to ensure long-term stability in Bosnia-Herzegovina," said EU
Commissioner Hans van den Broek.
</P>
<P>
The 15-nation union will also provide human resources for the
September 13-14 elections. It has deployed 2,450 election
supervisors in Bosnia as part of the Organization for Security and
Cooperation in Europe elections supervision mission.
</P>
<P>
A delegation from the European Parliament will monitor the
elections in Sarajevo, Banja Luka and Brcko.
</P>
<P>
EU assistance in the preparation for the municipal elections
started this spring when EU long-term supervisors arrived in
Bosnia and were joined soon after by their medium-term colleagues
who helped oversee the registration of 2.5 million voters.
</P>
<P>
EU is also providing the money to provide voter education
materials for the registration and polling processes in Bosnia and
the surrounding areas.
</P>
<P>
An EU source said the union is glad to see that Bosnian Croats
are no longer threatening to boycott the coming elections.
</P>
<P>
For the past two weeks, the Bosnian Croats and Serbs have been
threatening to boycott the municipal elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
