<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets with United Nations FAO Official  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The current food and
agricultural situation in the world, and China's cooperation with
the United Nations on these issues were the themes of talks
between Chinese Premier Li Peng and Dr. Jacques Diouf,
director-general of the UN Food and Agricultural Organization
(FAO) here today.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting in Zhongnanhai, the headquarters of the
central government, Premier Li said that the global food and
agricultural situation has been greatly improved in recent
years. However, he added, the situation still remains grim as long
as 800 million people in the world are starving or malnourished.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the World Food Summit, held by FAO last November,
adopted a Rome declaration on world food security and a plan of
action, saying that this has been of great importance for
increasing the international community's concern and support for
the food issue, promoting international cooperation in the food
and agricultural field, and raising world food production.
</P>
<P>
The premier briefed Dr. Diouf on the food and agriculture
issues in China. He said that since China is a huge agricultural
country, a stable agricultural sector plays a vital role in the
country's economic growth and social stability.
</P>
<P>
He said China will rely on three things to develop its
agriculture: good policy, science and technology, and input, and
that China will modernize its agriculture in the future. "China's
agriculture has a bright future," he added.
</P>
<P>
Noting that China supports 22 percent of the world population
with just seven percent of the arable land in the world, he
stressed that China has made the greatest contribution to global
food security.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese people are not only able to be self-sufficient,
but are also an important force to secure world food security," he
said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970912.0117 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets with United Nations FAO Official  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Moreover, Premier Li appreciated the FAO for its long-term
cooperation with China. He also thanked the organization for
providing technological assistance to the country for the
development of its agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Diouf warmly congratulated the 15th National Congress of
the Communist Party of China (CPC), which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
China's great achievements in obtaining a secure food situation
have drawn worldwide attention, he said, adding that the country's
experience is worth learning from for other developing countries.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Chinese people have not only been
self-supporting, but also provided food-related aid to other
developing countries and contributed to food security in the world.
</P>
<P>
He recalled with delight his meeting with Li in Rome last
November. He also thanked the Chinese Government for its support
for FAO.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Diouf and his party arrived here for a visit to China at
the invitation of the Chinese Ministry of Agriculture.  
