<HEADLINE> First Double-Decker Passenger Train Launched in Xinjiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, September 12 (Xinhua) -- A double-decker passenger
train went into service today between Urumqi, the capital of the
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, and the city of Kuitun.
</P>
<P>
It is the first Chinese double-decker operating on the Second
Eurasian Continental Bridge railway, which starts at the city of
Lianyungang in east China's Jiangsu province, and ends in
Rotterdam, Netherland.
</P>
<P>
The train has been launched by the North Xinjiang Railway
Company to boost local tourism and is equipped with bars,
air-conditioning and luxury facilities.
</P>
<P>
The three hour, 36 minute-train ride to cover the 224 km-long
route is one hour shorter than the time on other trains.
</P>
<P>
The operation of the double-decker represents the first step by
local railway authorities to renovate and upgrade the Chinese
section of the continental bridge railway by raising the speed and
introducing new types of locomotives and compartments, according
to railway sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
