<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar ends Steady As Market Consolidates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar
finished steady against the U.S. dollar as market consolidated
after volatility Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed at 72.18 U.S. cents, almost level
with Thursday's close of 72.17, after trading in a range of 71.95
to 72.20.
</P>
<P>
"The Australian dollar had seen a very quiet day's trading
after the volatility of the market yesterday," said Macquarie
Bank's manager Mark O'Leary.
</P>
<P>
Market participants are now suggesting that a sixth easing in
monetary policy will most likely come after September quarter
Consumer Price Index data and after the Reserve Bank of
Australia's October board meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Reserve Bank has cut official interest rates five times
since July last year in a bid to boost economic growth.
</P>
<P>
On the cross-rates, the local unit ended at 87.04 up from 85.82
against yen and at 1.2874 from 1.2915 against mark.  
</P>
</TEXT>
