<HEADLINE> Egypt Raps Israeli Settlement Policies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The Egyptian parliamentary
body at the International Parliamentary Union (IPU) today
strongly criticized the Israeli settlement policies in the
occupied Arab territories, particularly in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
This criticism was made by Kamal el-Shazli, Egyptian Minister
of State for Parliamentary and Shura Council, in his statement at
today's meeting of the IPU 98th session, which opened here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Shazli underlined the necessity of ending these settlement
activities which had led to the stalling of the peace process
along the Palestinian-Israeli track.
</P>
<P>
He said the U.N. General Assembly had called for the immediate
and complete cessation of Israeli settlements. Instead, he said,
Israel chose to challenge the will of the international community
by beginning the construction of a new settlement at Har Homa in
East Jerusalem in March.
</P>
<P>
Israeli settlement policies, he added, were not restricted to
East Jerusalem, but covered other occupied Arab territories,
including the Syrian Golan Heighs.
</P>
<P>
Shazli reiterated that the acts of aggression on the part of
Israel cannot be tolerated by such justifications as security or
combat of terrorism.
</P>
<P>
"Violence," he said, "will only beget violence, besides the
fact that the Palestinian leadership has expressed complete
readiness to security coordination with Israel."
</P>
<P>
The IPU is holding its 98th session in Cairo to discuss issues
related to security and cooperation in the Mediterranean region,
peace in the Middle East and other affairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
