<HEADLINE> Zanzibar Stresses Prevention of HIV/AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The government will
continue to maintain its main strategy on prevention of HIV
infection by providing education to promote sustained
behaviorable change of sexual abstinence and mutual fidelity.
</P>
<P>
This was stated by Omar Mapuri, Deputy Chief Minister and
Minister for Education of Zanzibar while inaugurating the Isles
annual anti-AIDS campaign with a main theme to protect children
against the epidemic on Thursday, according to a news dispatch
reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
About a fifth of the 150,000 children below six years in
Zanzibar have been infected with HIV, and the actual figure could
be higher as many cases went unreported, said Mapuri.
</P>
<P>
Most of the HIV carrying children have been infected through
breast-feeding or during the pregnance period, according to
Mapuri.
</P>
<P>
The inauguration of the Isles anti-AIDS campaign is part of
the international AIDS campaign whichnational reaches its climax on
December 1 each year.
</P>
<P>
Last year's world AIDS reports indicate that about 2.6
million children aged below 18 years had been infected with the
epidemic and most of them were from third world countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
