<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Down On Wall Street Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market
closed down today, driven lower by a fall on Wall Street and the
absence of an interest rate cut.
</P>
<P>
"That downwards movement on the Dow Jones had a spin-off effect
on the market combined with the fact that we did not get a rate
cut today," said Scott Emms from Henderson Charlton.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed overnight down 58.30 at
7,660.98.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index closed 25.8 points down at 2,640.0,
while the all industrials index was 27.1 points lower at 4,297.0.
</P>
<P>
The all resources eased 26.7 points to 1,341.5.
</P>
<P>
As copper prices on the London Metal Exchange fell nearly 50
U.S. dollars to a low for the year, key mining and resource stocks
here all closed down, with BHP 51 cents lower, Rio Tinto 44.5
cents down and WMC 25.4 cents weaker.
</P>
<P>
