<HEADLINE> 40th Anniversary Of Southwest China Autonomous Prefecture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The State Council, China's
top governing body, and the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress (NPC) have congratulated the Diqing Tibet
Autonomous Prefecture of Yunnan province on its 40th anniversary.
</P>
<P>
They sent their regards to the many ethnic groups and the armed
forces stationed in the prefecture, praising their achievements in
the last four decades.
</P>
<P>
The State Council and the NPC Standing Committee said they hope
the prefecture will make new progress in economic construction and
social development under the guidance of Deng Xiaoping's theory of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The Diqing Tibet Autonomous Prefecture is located at the
juncture of Sichuan and Yunnan provinces and the Tibet Autonomous
Region, and has 25 ethnic minorities in it.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 40 years, the prefecture has put 2,000 km of
highways to use and 60 percent of the villages are connected by
highways, and it has a computer-controlled telecommunications
network and power plants with a combined generating capacity of
80,000 kw.
</P>
<P>
Per capita income of farmers is 599 yuan, eight times the 1956
figure, just before the prefecture was founded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
