<HEADLINE> Drug Addicts Increase in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 12 (Xinhua) -- In Malaysia, 30 people
in a day or 887 in a month are addicted to drugs, according to
statistics released by the National Narcotics Agency today.
</P>
<P>
Agency Director Yaacob Mohd Amin said in a statement today that
in the first half of this year, 11,933 drug addicts were detected,
of whom 6,611 are repeat cases and 5,322 were new addicts.
</P>
<P>
Of the new addicts, 5,242 are male and the rest are female.
Among them, 1,945 are addicted to heroine, 1,683 to ganja (hemp),
1,265 to morphine and the rest to opium and other drugs, the
director said.
</P>
<P>
Yaacob said the number of new addicts dwindled in almost all
states except in Terengganu, Perlis and Sabah.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the January-June period, 877 drug peddlers
were detained under Section 39 (B) of the Dangerous Drugs Act
which carries a mandatory death sentence upon conviction.
</P>
<P>
Another 1,339 were arrested under Section 39 (A) of the same
Act for possession which carries a life imprisonment, he said.
</P>
<P>
A sum of 155.1 kilograms of heroine, 98.7 kilograms of raw
opium, 2.3 kilograms of marijuana and 159,284 psychotropic pills
were seized during the period, he said.
</P>
<P>
The official added there were 10,046 addicts undergoing
rehabilitation at 27 rehabilitation centers throughout Malaysia.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
