<HEADLINE> Chinese Mobile Phone Maker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 12 (Xinhua) -- China's leading producer of
mobile telecommunications equipment, Eastern Communications Co.
Ltd., plans to increase annual sales to 10 billion yuan by the end
of the century.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the Board of Directors Shi Jixing told Xinhua
recently that his company also aims to gradually replacing
Motorola with its own 'Eastcom' brand.
</P>
<P>
China's first cellular phone assembly line was built by Eastern
using technology from Motorola Inc., one of the world's leaders in
wireless communications and advanced electronics equipment.
</P>
<P>
Currently, one in six mobile phones in China is made by
Eastern, which is based in East China's Hangzhou.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, company sales exceeded four billion yuan, with 320
million yuan in profits. The company now has a total
capitalization of over 10 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
As China's only state-owned producer of mobile
telecommunications, Eastern is "a pillar of China's modern
telecommunications industry", according to Shi, who showed
confidence in his company's future and its ability to compete in
the international market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
