<HEADLINE> Shanghai GDP on Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Recent statistics show that
Shanghai, China's major trade and financial city, recorded a 13.3
percent increase in its August gross domestic product (GDP), with
the final figure standing at 27.4 billion yuan (3.3 billion US
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Statistics Bureau reports that city's August
industrial output-sales ratio stood at 98.2 percent, the highest
level since the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
Investments in fixed assets has also rebounded in August to end
at 12 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The city's export volume stood at 1.26 billion US dollars, up
9.8 percent on a year-on-year basis.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's total GDP for the past eight months hit 209.2
billion yuan, up 13.3 percent on last year's same period.
</P>
<P>
The city is expected to easily reach a projected economic
growth rate of 12 percent for the year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
