<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Second Phase Project on Jingyuan Power Plant Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The second-phase project of
Sino-US jointly funded Jingyuan Thermal Power Plant was recently
completed in northwest China's Gansu Province, with the capacity
of the two newly installed generating units standing at 600,000 kw.
</P>
<P>
Local sources report that the generators have been linked to
the local power grid.
</P>
<P>
The power plant, part of the Jingyuan Coal Mine, previously had
a combined generating capacity of 800,000 kw.
</P>
<P>
In 1993, the government and WUS-based Westinghouse announced a
decision to invest 2.5 billion yuan in a project to ease power
shortages in northwest China. The joint Jingyuan plant expansion
project called for the installation of two 300,000-kw generating
units. Westinghouse holds a 30 percent share of the venture.
</P>
<P>
Jingyuan, a fully computerized thermal power plant which is the
largest of its kind in Gansu Province, employees 500 technicians.
</P>
<P>
The two generating units which have passed rigorous test
related to technical design standards and parameters, are
currently in commercial operation. Third generating unit is in
the trial operation stage.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
