<HEADLINE> Sino-American MBA Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 12 (Xinhua) -- China's first MBA program,
jointly established by Fudan University School of Administration
and the Sloan School of Business at the Massachusetts Institute of
Technology, premiered today in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Fudan University President Yang Fujia, and US consular in
Shanghai Bruce Nelson attended the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The MBA program was established on the basis of a five-year
cooperative agreement signed in June 1996.
</P>
<P>
The Sloan School of Business, one of most prominent business
schools in the United States, will provide textbooks, reference
materials and visiting lecturers for the program.
</P>
<P>
Fudan has enrolled 40 students in the first MBA class. 
