<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ECOMOG Warns S. Leone Junta Against Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The west African peacekeeping
force known as ECOMOG Thursday warned Sierra Leone's military
junta not to launch new attacks or to face the consequences of
its action.
</P>
<P>
The warning came after new attacks on ECOMOG positions by the
junta, the Daily Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
Anti-aircraft troops the junta deployed at the port opened
fire at an ECOMOG jet fighter, which junta spokesman Aliu Kamara
said dropped a bomb and killed two persons.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman denied that the junta had launched aggression on
ECOMOG troops based in the capital Freetown, adding that "We are
firing at them heavily for them to know that we are alert. We are
not going to take chance at all."
</P>
<P>
"As a responsible government, we have to establish ourselves,
let these people understand that this is our territorial
integrity. We are a sovereign state," he added.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman described the regular petrols of ECOMOG planes
to enforce economic embargo as actions "to intimidate our people,
to provoke us, making life uneasy for our people".
</P>
<P>
However, in a strongly worded statement, ECOMOG force
Commander Major-General Victor Malu warned the junta that
aircraft under his command would return fire if attack breaks out
over Freetown.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the junta has deployed anti-aircraft guns in
civilian populated areas, Malu advised the civilians to "move out
of the areas if the junta fails to remove the weapons from their
midst".
</P>
<P>
Malu also expressed concern that the junta had virtually
turned the Freetown seaport into a military base, using the port
facilities as weapons and ammunition storage.
</P>
<P>
This is not the first time the junta accused of ECOMOG planes
bombing the port in Freetown since ECOMOG announced that it would
attack any violators of the embargo a week ago.
</P>
<P>
The embargo was approved by west African leaders at a summit
last month to try to force the junta, which seized power in a
coup in May, to step down. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
