<HEADLINE> Australia Pledges to Help Stabilize ASEAN Currencies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Australian Treasurer
Peter Costello said here today that his country is ready to
cooperate in any new package to stabilize the currency situation
in the Southeast Asian region.
</P>
<P>
Costello said a stable stock market and currency market in
ASEAN countries is as much in Australia's interest as it is for
the region.
</P>
<P>
It is important for the region to have stable currencies and
stock markets so that it can pursue economic development to the
greatest extent, he told reporters after meeting Malaysian Deputy
Prime Minister and Finance Minister Anwar Ibrahim.
</P>
<P>
Sydney has already committed 1 billion U.S. dollars to the 16
billion U.S.-dollar International Monetary Fund rescue package to
stabilize the Thai baht, he said.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with Anwar, Costello exchanged views with
him on economic prospects in the region, including the latest
developments in the currency and stock markets.
</P>
<P>
Costello said Australia and Malaysia reaffirmed their strong
bond.
</P>
<P>
He said he and Anwar will meet again in Hong Kong when they
attend the World Bank and International Monetary Fund conference
scheduled for September 23 and 25.
</P>
<P>
Costello arrived here last night for a two-day visit.  
</P>
</TEXT>
