<HEADLINE> Guangxi Posts and Telecommunications </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Every 200 people in south
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region currently have access to
seven telephones and one cellular phone.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi's posts and telecommunications sector recorded a total
business volume of 1.71 billion yuan and earnings of 1.68 billion
yuan in the first half of the year, up 36.11 percent and 37.3
percent respectively compared with the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Some 184,800 telephone numbers and 58,800 cellular phone
subscribers were added in the first half of this year. The
business volume for long-distance, local and mobile
telecommunications accounted for 29.83 percent, 27.69 percent and
35.27 percent of the total respectively.  
</P>
