<HEADLINE> HK Press Publish Commentaries Hailing Opening of CPC Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 12 (Xinhua) -- A host of Hong Kong
newspapers published commentaries today hailing the opening of the
15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
Entitled "An Important Meeting Convened at An Important Time",
a commentary carried by Wen Wei Po said that the meeting has the
significance of inheriting the past and ushering in the future,
carrying the cause forward and forging ahead into the future.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will hold high the banner of the late Chinese
leader Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics, review the history of the Chinese people's
struggles in the past century and look forward to China's
development in the first half of next century, and work out
overall arrangements for the cross-century construction and
development of China, said the paper.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the congress will elect the new central leading
bodies to lead the nation into the 21st century, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The commentary noted that the five years closely following the
14th CPC congress were the five years which saw the most rapid
increase in China's comprehensive national power, the most stable
society and the most obvious improvement in people's livelihood in
this century.
</P>
<P>
The tremendous achievements scored during the five years
demonstrated that major decisions made at the 14th congress were
correct and that the third generation of CPC's leadership with
Chinese President Jiang Zemin at its core was leading effectively
the Chinese people in their striding forward along the path of
building Socialism with Chinese characteristics, the commentary
continued.
</P>
<P>
The five years following the current congress are of critical
importance to China's cross-century development. Within the five
years, centering on the economic construction, the economic
structure reforms, political structure reforms and the
ideological and ethical construction will be further promoted,
laying sound foundation for realizing the objectives set for the
end of the century and the long-term objectives set for the year
2010, the commentary added.
</P>
<P>
A commentary published by Hong Kong Commercial Daily said that,
With Hong Kong's return to its motherland, Hong Kong people are
paying closer than ever attention to the 15th CPC congress, which
concerns the nation's future and destiny.
</P>
<P>
People can believe that the congress will be a new landmark in
China's modernization drive and that the CPC is capable of leading
the people to build a better China, it said.
</P>
<P>
Ta Kung Pao's commentary noted that the congress is the first
major issue in the Chinese people's political life following Hong
Kong's handover on July 1, and of course it attracts great
attention from Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
It quoted a recent poll of Hong Kong residents as saying that
Hong Kong people have cast a vote of confidence toward the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
According to the poll, around 65 percent of the respondents
said the meeting is important to Hong Kong's development, close to
60 percent expected politics to be more open in the inland areas
after the meeting while close to 70 percent people predicted a
better economic development in the inland areas.
</P>
<P>
Other major Chinese newspapers such as Ming Pao Daily News,
Sing Tao Daily and Express News also published commentaries on the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
News about the congress has recently been the focus of the
local media, with a large number of Hong Kong reporters sent to
Beijing to cover the week-long meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
