<HEADLINE> '97 China Investment, Trade Fair Opens in Xi'an </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The '97 China Xi'an Investment
and Trade Fair opened today in the capital of northwest China's
Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The fair, which is being held in the Shaanxi Industrial
Exhibition Hall, has attracted more than 1,000 overseas and
domestic businessmen from over 20 countries and regions, including
the United States, Japan, and Canada.
</P>
<P>
The city government predicts that pledged foreign investments
will exceed 250 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Local governments are anticipating foreign investments in some
116 projects in 11 industrial sectors, including urban
infrastructure, agriculture, machine-building, electronics,
pharmaceuticals and real estate. Total investments are expected to
reach 19.3 billion yuan (2.3 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Basic infrastructure, agricultural, and production projects
will attract 76 percent of total investments. Local officials said
that Xian will also auction a number of properties as part of the
reform of state-owned enterprises. 
</P>
