<HEADLINE> 22 Killed in Fierce Fighting in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Ten government troops and 12
Tamil rebels were killed in fierce fighting Thursday at
Puliyankulam in Sri Lanka's Northeast Province, military sources
said today.
</P>
<P>
The rebels fired mortars and artillery on the government troops
guarding the area, killing 10 soldiers and injuring 67 others.
</P>
<P>
The government troops returned fire immediately.
</P>
<P>
The military said 12 rebels were also killed and a large number
of others injured.  
</P>
</TEXT>
