<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ugandan Rebels Kill 21 Civilians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Twentyone civilians were
killed Thursday when Uganda's rebel Allied Democratic Forces
(ADF) raided Nyahuka at the western border with democratic Congo,
said a report reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Fifty ADF rebels attacked a camp at Nyahuka in the morning and
the Uganda army reacted immediately, said the report quoting
Chief of the army Staff Chefe Ali. The government troops were
pursueing the rebels last night, he added.
</P>
<P>
Eight rebels have been killed in the battle. Two policemen
were killed in the battle.
</P>
<P>
ADF, which reportedly has 15,000 fighters last November, often
made operations in western Uganda with some of the rebels are
hiding in the Rwenzori Mountain bordering democratic Congo.
</P>
</TEXT>
