<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, September 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia welcomes Bosnian Serbs' final decision to
participate in the local elections scheduled for September 13-14
in Bosnia, a spokesman from the Foreign Ministry said here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The elections, which were provided for in the Dayton peace
agreement signed in 1995, constitute an important step to promote
the Bosnian peace process, hoping that they will be held smoothly,
said the spokesman. (Russia-Bosnia-Local Elections)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW YORK -- As Asia becomes increasingly important in the
international scene, the United States and Asia must work
together, Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region Tung Chee-Hwa said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a dinner hosted by the Economic Club of New York,
Tung said Asia's economic and political impact on the world in the
decades to come cannot be overlooked and "must be seen in a
favorable manner by the United States." He forecast that Asia
could have an economy larger than the North American Free Trade
Agreement countries or the European Union in the next century.
(US-Tung-Asia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- The 15th National Congress of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) opened at the Great Hall of the People in Beijing
Friday Morning.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin delivered, on behalf of the 14th Central Committee,
a report entitled "Hold High the Great Banner of Deng Xiaoping
Theory For an All-Round Advancement of the Cause of Building
Socialism With Chinese Characteristics" at the opening session.
(China-CPC Congress-Opening)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- South Korea and Japan failed to narrow their
differences over rewriting a 1965 bilateral fisheries accord at a
two-day meeting here Thursday, local media reported.
</P>
<P>
During the fifth round of fishery talks this year, the two
sides put forward their respective proposals and made no major
differences in their positions, according to Shin Jung-seung,
South Korea's chief delegate to the talks. (S.Korea-Japan-Talks)
</P>
</TEXT>
