<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia Suffers Defeat in U.S. Open Quarter-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia suffered severe
setback at the U.S. Open badminton tournament as three of its ace
men's shuttlers were beaten in the men's singles quarter-finals
at Orange, California, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
World number 10 Hermawan Susanto lost 15-9, 15-5 to
giant-killer Jeroen van Dijk of the Netherlands who earlier
eliminated reigning world champion Peter Rasmussen of Denmark.
</P>
<P>
Alan Budi Kusuma of Indonesia also bowed out of the
competitions after losing to Peter Gade-Christensen of Denmark
17-18, 15-2, 17-14.
</P>
<P>
Marleve Mainaky, the third Indonesian shuttler in the men's
singles quarter-finals, was beaten by second-seeded Poul-Erik
Hoyer-Larsen of Denmark 15-9, 15-6.
</P>
<P>
The only Asian shuttler left in the men's singles semi-finals
is Luo Yigang of China who booked his berth with a 15-11, 15-7
win over Thomas Stuer-Lauridsen of Denmark.
</P>
<P>
In the women's singles, the top four seeds all sailed into the
semi-finals after scoring their respective quarter-final
victories.
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Camilla martina of Denmark downed Kelly Morgan of
Wales 11-4, 11-5.
</P>
<P>
Han Jingna of China, the third seed at the tournament, dropped
her first set 10-12 against Japanese Takako Ida but fougth back
to wrap up the match 11-2, 11-2 in the second and third sets.
</P>
<P>
Fourth-seeded Marina Andrievskaya of Sweden also entered the
semi-finals with a 11-0, 11-4 easy win over Mette pedersen of
Denmark.
</P>
<P>
The last women's singles semi-final berth was taken by
second-seed Dai Yun of China who saw off Cindy Shi of the United
States 11-10, 11-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
