<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand
sharemarket drifted lower in moderate trading volume today and
lower forest stocks contributed to the fall.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended four points lower at 2,483 with a
turnover of 62 million NZ dollars (39 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Fletcher Energy shares reversed their rise in the past two
days, closing down 12 cents to 650 cents on profit taking. Also
lower were Carter Holt Harvey, dropping 2 cents to 333 cents, and
Fletcher Paper, diving 8 cents to 295 cents. Other weaker leaders
included Air New Zealand, dipping 1 cent to 283 cents and Lion
Nathan, losing 6 cents to 374 cents.
</P>
<P>
Telecom shares gained 4 cents to 786 cents while Brierley
Investment remained unchanged at 128 cents.  
</P>
