<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canadian Boileau Wins Gold in Platform Event </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Myriam Boileau of Canada
came back from behind to win the women's 10-meter platform gold
medal at the 10th World Diving Cup competition here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Boileau finished with 352.23 points and was trailed by Chinese
divers Wang Rui with 347.10 points and Chi Bin with 330.18.
</P>
<P>
On her fourth of five dives in the final, the 19-year-old
Boileau gained 80.04 points -- the highest score so far in this
competition and finished her final dive with 74.76 to take the
title.
</P>
<P>
It was the first gold medal at a major diving competition for a
Canadian since Sylvie Bernier won the 3-meter springboard at the
1984 Olympics.
</P>
<P>
China won three of the four gold medal presented so far in the
competition Thursday when Gong Ming and Xu Hao finished with
332.91 points to win the 3-meter synchronized springboard event.
</P>
<P>
The World Cup Diving competitions will go through
Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
