<DOCNO> XIE19970912.0211 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 4,800 Loans Granted for Housing in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's State Mortgage
and Investment Bank granted 4,800 housing loans amounting to 700
million rupees (11.9 million U.S. dollars) during the first eight
months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The amount represents an increase of about 40 percent over the
same period of last year, bank sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The loans ranged from 170 dollars to 85,000 dollars and the
quantum depended on the repayment capability of the applicant.
</P>
<P>
Loan applicants were mostly teachers, corporation employees,
service personnel and businessmen.
</P>
<P>
The bank has recorded a loan recovery rate of 80 percent.
</P>
<P>
Loans can be obtained from the bank for the purchase of a
building site, house renovations and electricity and water
supplies.
</P>
<P>
In addition they are granted for the purchase of agricultural
machinery, tractors and trucks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
