<HEADLINE> Iran Upsets Philippines in Asian Basketball Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Iran pulled off the biggest
upset of Thursday as it downed the Philippines 77-76 at the final
buzzer in the Asian men's basketball championship in Riyadh, Saudi
Arabia.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines looked to have the game in control early on,
but the lead dwindled to 38-35 at he half as Iran engineered a
comeback.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, Iran took the lead briefly. The two sides
exchanged volleys of baskets and the lead several times before the
Philippines built a slim lead as time wound down.
</P>
<P>
In the final seconds, Iran trailed by two points before sinking
a three point shot to win the Group A game. The Iranian players
rejoiced and some wept.
</P>
<P>
In the other Group A game, 10-time champion China beat Bahrain
74-60.
</P>
<P>
In Group B, South Korea trounced Bangladesh 153-55 and the
United Arab Emirates overcame India 82-65
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia downed Hong Kong 84-58 in Group C, Jordan edged
Kazakhstan 66-65 and Indonesia beat Chinese Taipei 75-50 in Group
D. 
</P>
