<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Finances Water Management in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
approved a 51 million U.S. dollars loan to finance a Brazilian
water resources management project in the State of Bahia, the
poorest region of the country.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be used to strengthen the infrastructure for
effective water resources management, a key to future economic
development of the region which is plagued by cyclical droughts.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to improve the environment of
surrounding areas and therefore benefit water consumers in urban
and rural districts.
</P>
<P>
The estimated total cost of the project is about 85 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
A 30 million dollars loan will provide technical and financial
means for improving the efficiency of institutions involved in
water resources management in the State.
</P>
<P>
Fifty-five million dollars will finance the construction and
rehabilitation of water resources storage and distribution
infrastructure in the Itapicuru River Basin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
