<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Supports Projects in Togo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
approved two credits valued at a total of 55.2 million
U.S. dollars to back agricultural and transport projects in Togo.
</P>
<P>
The first credit of 19.2 million dollars will go to assist Togo
National Agricultural Services Support Project. The project is
designed to improve standards of living of farm households by
increasing agricultural productivity and production.
</P>
<P>
It will be carried out by improving the efficiency of
agricultural research and extension services, making them more
responsive to farmers' needs and improving access to rural credit,
especially for poor farmers.
</P>
<P>
Another credit of 36 million dollars is earmarked for Togo's
road transport project. This project will focus on rehabilitating
and maintaining existing road infrastructure and strengthening the
management capacity of transport institutions.
</P>
<P>
The credits will be channeled through the International
Development Association (IDA), the World Bank's concessionary
lending arm for developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
