<HEADLINE> World Bank Loan for Hungary Jobs Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
approved a loan valued at 60.1 million U.S. dollars for a project in
Hungary designed to reduce unemployment among young adults.
</P>
<P>
The Youth Training Project will provide equipment, software,
technical assistance and training to expand work selection and
work training for young people who have left school.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be at a fixed interest rate for 15 years,
including a five-year grace period. The project will be carried
out over three years.  
</P>
