<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Private TV Channels To Be Operative Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Private channels of Bangladesh
Television (BTV) will be operative soon, sources said today.
</P>
<P>
Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina has already approved
the draft policies for the establishment of private television
channels in the country, the sources quoted State Minister for
Information Abu Sayeed as saying.
</P>
<P>
The minister said the government is also considering giving
permission to private radio channels.
</P>
<P>
A reporting team of the BTV would be organized and it would be
working round-the-clock, he said, adding that a new van has been
procured for out-door direct telecasting of programs.
</P>
<P>
The government had also decided to increase the "rate of the
official advertisement," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, 22 companies have applied to set up
private television channels in the country.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh would uphold its heritage and tradition, the
minister stressed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
