<HEADLINE> World Bank Supports Morocco Second Municipal Finance Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
approved the financing of 35 million U.S. dollars and 205 million
French franc for the Second Municipal Finance Project in Morocco.
</P>
<P>
The project is designed to improved living standards of about 4
million people living in small and medium-sized rural and urban
communes. It will also integrate these communes into the modern
economy.
</P>
<P>
This will be implemented by increasing the provision of basic
infrastructure services in these cities and by strengthening Fonds
d'Equipment Communal as a commercially viable, autonomous
financial institution specialized into providing financial
services to the municipal sector. 
</P>
