<HEADLINE> Russia Welcomes Serbs' Participation in Local Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 11 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman from the Foreign
Ministry, Gennady Tarasov, said today that Russia welcomes Bosnian
Serbs' final decision to participate in the local elections
scheduled for September 13-14 in Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
At a news conference, Tarasov said the elections constitute an
important step to promote the Bosnian peace process, hoping that
they will be held smoothly.
</P>
<P>
Tarasov also expressed his concern about earlier boycott
decisions by Bosnian Serbs and Croats, saying that it would
threaten the elections all over Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
The local elections are provided for in the Dayton peace
agreement signed in 1995. The Serbs and Croats' boycott has evoked
protest from Britain and Germany Wednesday. 
</P>
