<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 15th CPC National Congress Opens (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang Zemin delivered, on behalf of the 14th Central Committee,
a report entitled "Hold High the Great Banner of Deng Xiaoping
Theory For an All-Round Advancement of the Cause of Building
Socialism With Chinese Characteristics" at the opening session.
</P>
<P>
He described the current congress as an extremely important
congress.
</P>
<P>
"Held at the turn of the century to break new ground for the
future, it will ensure that the whole Party will carry out
Comrade Deng Xiaoping's behests and march unswervingly and
triumphantly along the correct line adopted since the Third
Plenary Session of the Eleventh Central Committee," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang stressed that the theme of the congress is to hold high
the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory for an all-round
advancement of the cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics to the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
In the Great Hall of the People, the venue of the congress, a
huge streamer bearing the characters of "The 15th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China" was hung in the front of
the rostrum. The party emblem was flanked by bright-coloured party
flags. The hall was also decorated with streamers reading "Holding
high the Great Banner of Building Socialism with Chinese
Characteristics and advancing the Great Cause of Building
Socialism into the 21st Century" and "Long Live the Great,
Glorious and Correct Communist Party of China".
</P>
<P>
Sitting on the rostrum were members of the Standing Committee
of the Congress Presidium, including Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi, Li
Ruihuan, Zhu Rongji, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao, Ding Guangen, Tian
Jiyun, Li Lanqing, Li Tieying, Yang Baibing, Wu Bangguo, Zou
Jiahua, Jiang Chunyun, Qian Qichen, Huang Ju, Wei Jianxing, Xie
Fei, Wen Jiabao, Wang Hanbin, Yang Shangkun, Wan Li, Song Ping, Bo
Yibo, Zhang Zhen, Zhang Wannian, Chi Haotian, Ren Jianxin, Ye
Xuanping, Wu Xueqian and Hou Zongbin.
</P>
<P>
The opening session, presided over by Li Peng, opened at 9:00
this morning amid the music played by the military band with all
present standing and singing the National Anthem.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
