<DOCNO> XIE19970912.0236 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 15th CPC National Congress Opens (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang Zemin expounded the primary stage of socialism and how to
build socialism in this primary stage. He pointed out that the
primary stage means the undeveloped stage. The development level
of the productive forces in China determines that the country must
accomplish industrialization and socialization,
market-orientation and modernization of the economy. The primary
stage of socialism is a considerably long period of time.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed out the key to accomplish the tasks for the
current Party congress and advance the cause to the 21st century
is to adhere to, consolidate and improve the leadership of the
Party and Party building.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the importance of strengthening the Party's
ideological, organizational building and style of work.
</P>
<P>
In conclusion, Jiang called on the entire Party to
hold high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory, closely rally
around the CPC Central Committee, work hard unyieldingly and with
one heart and one mind and carry forward in an all-round way the
great cuase of building socilaism with Chinese characteristics to
the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's report was punctuated by warm applauses for many times.
</P>
<P>
Rong Yiren, vice-president of the People's Republic of China,
was also invited to attend the Party congress along with
non-communists who are vice-chairmen of the National People's
Congress Standing Committee, the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultaive Conference (CPPCC), non-Communist
parties and leaders of All-China Federation of Industry and
Commerce and people with no party affiliations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
