<HEADLINE> Bosnian Serb Government Ends Boycott of Local Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The Bosnian Serb Assembly
approved a government decision to participate in the local
elections this weekend.
</P>
<P>
The assembly at a meeting Wednesday also urged electoral
constituencies to call on eligible voters to cast their ballots.
</P>
<P>
However, the assembly reserved the rights to boycott the
election in constituencies where fraudulent practices might occur.
</P>
<P>
Johan Fernande, spokesman for the high representative for
Bosnia of the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe
(OSCE) expressed his satisfaction with the assembly's decision to
end boycott of the elections.
</P>
<P>
Except those war criminals who have been charged by the Hague
International Court of Justice, no one should be arrested at
polling stations on September 13 and 14, Fernande added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
