<HEADLINE> Hebei Hooked Up With Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The telecommunication
department of Hebei Province in north China has set up an Internet
web site to provide global computer network access to the public.
</P>
<P>
The service provider's move is aimed at connecting the province
with other parts of the world via a computer network.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of customers have already registered to be hooked up
with the network, and the proportion of individual and unit
customers each stand at 50 percent.
</P>
<P>
More than 30 government departments have become the network's
first group of customers, and an Internet club is to be set up by
the service provider, with an investment of more than three
million yuan (about 370,000 US dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
