<DOCNO> XIE19970912.0253 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin on Achievements over Past Five Years (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New breakthroughs have been made in the reform and opening to
the outside world. In accordance with the requirements for
establishing a socialist market economy, we took big strides in
reforming the systems of finance, taxation, banking, foreign
trade, foreign exchange, planning, investment, pricing,
circulation, housing and social security. Market forces notably
served as the basic means of regulating the allocation of
resources, and the framework of a macroeconomic control system was
preliminarily established, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
China pressed forward with the reform in state-owned
enterprises after making experiments in selected ones. The country
further developed the pattern with the public sector remaining
dominant and diverse sectors of the economy developing side by
side.
</P>
<P>
"We continued to expand economic and technological cooperation
and exchanges with other countries, effected big increases in
foreign trade and in the use of foreign funds and brought about a
marked rise in state foreign exchange reserves," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
China has taken new steps in promoting cultural and ethical
progress. Gratifying achievements were scored in science,
technology, education, culture, public health, sports, family
planning and other social undertakings. Significant progress was
made in developing socialist democracy and improving the legal
system.
</P>
<P>
The great unity of all China's nationalities was further
consolidated and developed. Social and political unity and
stability provided an important guarantee for the reform and
development, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Progress was made in modernizing national defense. The combat
effectiveness of the army was further enhanced.
</P>
<P>
He said that the living standards of the people rose notably.
The average annual per capita income for living expenses increased
by 7.2 percent for city dwellers in real terms, while the average
annual per capita net income went up by 5.7 percent for rural
residents in real terms, making the period one of those with the
biggest increases. The people's living conditions including food,
clothing, housing, articles for daily use and transportation
improved markedly. The rural poor population of the country
decreased by 32 million, he said.
</P>
<P>
In the past five years, Jiang said, "we have done a great deal
of work with marked results in the peaceful reunification of the
motherland. The Chinese government has resumed the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong, which has wiped out the century-old
humiliation of the Chinese nation."
</P>
<P>
This is a great event which makes every Chinese elated and has
won universal acclaim from the international community, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Party general secretary said that China has stepped up
efforts to strengthen Party building. The whole Party studied more
and more deeply Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics. Progress was made in strengthening
leading bodies and the contingent of cadres, with a large number
of fine young cadres taking leading posts.
</P>
<P>
"We redoubled our efforts to improve the Party's work style,
build clean government and fight corruption and achieved successes
by stages," he added.
</P>
<P>
On the shortcomings and defects in the work of the past five
years, Jiang said, the quality and efficiency of the national
economy as a whole remain fairly low, the irrational economic
structure still poses a rather outstanding problem, and especially
part of the state-owned enterprises lack vitality.
</P>
<P>
The work style of the Party and the government, the current
social conduct and public security still fall short of the
expectations of the people, he added.
</P>
<P>
Uneven regional development is obvious, and part of the urban
and rural residents still live in straitened circumstances.
Population growth and economic development have caused great
strains on resources and the environment.
</P>
<P>
"We must pay great attention to these problems and solve them
in a down-to-earth way," he said.
</P>
<P>
The achievements scored in the five years are the outcome of
the united endeavor of the whole Party and the people throughout
the country, he said. They have provided valuable new experience
and will serve as a more solid foundation for our future
development. All this will greatly encourage us to win new
victories with greater confidence and enthusiasm," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970912.0254 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin on Party Building (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua ) -- Chinese Communist Party
leader Jiang Zemin called here today for upholding, strengthening
and improving the leadership of the Party and doing well in Party
building.
</P>
<P>
This is essential for holding high the great banner of Deng
Xiaoping Theory, fulfilling the tasks defined at this congress and
advancing the cause of building socialism with Chinese
Characteristics in an all-round way to the 21st century, he said.
</P>
<P>
The remarks were made by Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, at the opening
session of the 15th National Party Congress, which opened in
Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
The entire Party should strengthen its building in ideology,
organization, style of work and all other aspects, always try to
improve its leading and governing ability, and guard against
corruption and degeneration so as to show a new look and greater
militancy in leading the people in accomplishing the new
historical tasks, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
To strengthen Party building ideologically, it is essential to
unswervingly arm the entire Party with Deng Xiaoping Theory and
give full play to the ideological and political strength of the
Party. The entire Party should attach great importance to study,
be adept at studying and usher in a new upsurge in studying
Marxism-Leninism, Mao Zedong Thought and particularly Deng
Xiaoping Theory, he said.
</P>
<P>
Leading cadres at all levels, and especially the several
hundred members of the Party Central Committee and the several
thousand cadres at the provincial and ministerial levels bear a
specially important responsibility in holding high the great
banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory. They should take the lead in
studying that theory and comprehensively and accurately master its
scientific system. They should grasp both the basic ideas and the
essence of the theory in an overall perspective and systematically
analyze and understand the relevant aspects of the theory in light
of the respective fields of their work, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
To strengthen Party building organizationally, it is essential
to make the Party the core of strong leadership and give full play
to its organizational strength, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that under the conditions of reform, opening to the
outside world and developing a socialist market economy,
democratic centralism, instead of being weakened, must be improved
and developed.
</P>
<P>
It is a strategic task to train and select a large number of
excellent young cadres who can shoulder cross-century important
tasks, Jiang said, adding, "We must lose no time in fulfilling
this task. We should pay great attention to fostering and
promoting women cadres, cadres from among ethnic minorities and
non-Party cadres."
</P>
</TEXT>
