<HEADLINE> Leaders Praised for Smooth Economic Operation (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Renowned economists have
spoken highly of the leadership of the third generation of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) for its capability in coping with
complicated economic phenomena.
</P>
<P>
"Third generation leaders with Jiang Zemin at the core have
exhibited great foresight and superb skills in governing economic
operations to improve the overall situation since the 14th CPC
National Congress in 1992," said Professor Xiao Zhuoji of Beijing
University in a recent interview with Xinhua News Agency.
</P>
<P>
China is now making efforts to build socialism with Chinese
characteristics, and is undergoing a shift from a planned to a
market economy, as well as from extensive to intensive operations
in terms of its mode of economic growth.
</P>
<P>
New problems have kept cropping up in economic operation, he
said, while superficial ones have been solved, others will emerge,
accompanied by deep-rooted contradictions.
</P>
<P>
"Nonetheless, the collective leadership has taken up the
gauntlet at the turning point and has introduced a series of
far-reaching principles for economic construction and
restructuring, as well major policies to maintain rapid, sustained
and smooth economic development," he said.
</P>
<P>
China's GDP has maintained an annual average increase of 12.1
percent over the past five years, and in 1995 accomplished the
strategic target of quadrupling the 1980 GDP five years ahead of
schedule. The country's macroeconomic performance has entered the
best period since the 1990s with high growth rate and low
inflation.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970912.0256 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin on Party Building (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The primary Party organizations are the focus of all the
Party's work and the base of its fighting capacity. The work of
consolidating and improving primary Party organizations should be
geared to the Party's basic line and serve its central task.They
should study new situations and problems in a spirit of reform and
improve their methods and style of work and their ways of
conducting activities, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
To improve the Party's style of work, Jiang said, it is
essential to stick to the aim of serving the people wholeheartedly
and give full play to the Party's strength in forging close links
with the masses.
</P>
<P>
To work for the people's interests wholeheartedly is the
starting point as well as the purpose of all the work for building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, said Jiang, who also urged
Party members to listen to the opinions of the masses, help
alleviate their hardships and do practical things in their
interest.
</P>
<P>
Party cadres, especially leading cadres, must correctly
exercise the powers entrusted to them by the people and must
never abuse them for personal gain, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said, "the fight against corruption is a grave political
struggle vital to the very existence of the Party and the state."
</P>
<P>
"We should fight corruption and continuously give the warning
throughout the process of reform and opening to the outside
world.," he said, adding, "We should continue to make sure that
leading cadres are clean, honest and self-disciplined, investigate
and deal with major cases and rectify unsound practices in
departments and trades. Party committees at all levels must take a
clear-cut stand and firmly persevere in this work."
</P>
<P>
By deepening the reform, he said, "we should gradually
eradicate the hotbed for the breeding and spreading of
corruption." China should combine the fight against corruption
with the purification of Party organizations, never allowing
corruptionists to hide themselves within the Party, he stressed.
Tightening Party discipline is the guarantee for maintaining the
Party's advanced nature and purity and enhancing its cohesiveness
and fighting capacity, Jiang noted. Party committees at all levels
should adhere to the principle that "the Party should supervise
itself," carrying out the policy of tightening Party discipline in
all aspects of Party building, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
