<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Leaders Praised for Smooth Economic Operation (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
High-ranking leaders have managed to balance reform and
development, while simultaneously doing an excellent job in
promoting domestic development and opening, reforming existing and
developing new systems, raising overall national strength and
living standards, expanding market-oriented economy and enhancing
macro-control, said Xiao.
</P>
<P>
Hu Angang, a research fellow with the Chinese Academy of
Sciences, noted that third generation leaders have succeeded in
some areas in which the previous two generations of leaders failed
to do. Hu was referring to three major third generation
accomplishments since 1992: revenue sharing reform, macroeconomic
control, and narrowing the gap between eastern and western areas.
</P>
<P>
"The three accomplishments have been highly praised for
conforming with existing national conditions. The early success of
revenue sharing reform and the central government's strengthened
macro-control on finances led to the successful accomplishment of
an economic soft landing. Regional disparities aroused the serious
concern of third generation leaders, and efforts have been made to
accomplish common prosperity," said Hu.
</P>
<P>
Hu attributed the three accomplishments to the pragmatic
attitude of the leadership and their extensive research and
investigation efforts, as well as the wisdom of experts and
collective leadership both within and outside the Party.  
</P>
</TEXT>
