<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Official Calls for Countering Trade Barriers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Thai Deputy Prime Minister
Thaksin Shinawatra said on Thursday that trade in agricultural
goods in Southeast Asia must be boosted to counteract trade
barriers enforced by some developed nations.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with ministers of agriculture and forestry of
ASEAN nations, Thaksin said that because the Southeast Asian
region faces stiff competition from more advanced countries with
processing industries, the ASEAN must share both raw materials and
the latest technologies.
</P>
<P>
He added that ASEAN nations must act quickly to benefit from
currently weak currencies that made agricultural products cheaper
and increased the competitiveness of exports.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN ministers are here to participate in a two-day
ministerial meeting to discuss ASEAN agricultural products'
standards, the establishment of an ASEAN agricultural information
network and cooperation with the private sector.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is to close later today.  
</P>
