<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin on Economic Restructuring and Development Strategy (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- To establish a more or less
ideal socialist market economy and maintain a sustained, rapid and
sound development of the national economy are the two major tasks
for China, said Jiang Zemin today.
</P>
<P>
In his report delivered at the 15th National Party Congress
which opened here today, Jiang, general secretary of the Communist
Party of China Central Committee, said China must strive for new
breakthroughs in some major aspects of reform and make substantial
progress in optimizing the economic structure, developing science
and technology and raising the level of opening up to keep to the
orientation of building a socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
The move is to really find a way to coordinated development of
the economy featuring a fairly high speed, fairly good performance
and constant improvement of the quality of the economy as a whole,
he said.
</P>
<P>
In his report to the Party congress, Jiang elaborated the
strategies for China's economic restructuring and economic
development from eight major aspects: to readjust and improve the
ownership structure; accelerate the reform of state-owned
enterprises; improve the structure and mode of distribution; give
full play to the role of the market mechanism and improve the
macroeconomic control system; strengthen agriculture as the
foundation of the economy, and readjust and optimize the economic
structure; implement the strategies of developing the country by
relying on science and education and of achieving sustainable
development; strive to do better in opening to the outside world;
and continue to improve the standard of living of the people.
</P>
<P>
On the reform of state-owned enterprises, Jiang said the
establishment of a modern enterprise system is the orientation of
the reform of state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
He noted China will convert large and medium-sized state-owned
enterprises into standard corporations according to the
requirements of "clearly established ownership, well defined power
and responsibility, separation of enterprise from administration,
and scientific management" so that they will become corporate
entities and competitors adaptable to the market.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that China will define more clearly the powers and
responsibilities of the state and enterprises. The state will
enjoy the owner's equity according to the amount of capital it has
put into the enterprises and bear limited responsibilities for the
debts of enterprises while enterprises will operate independently
according to law, responsible for their own profits and losses.
</P>
<P>
The government should not directly intervene in the operation
of enterprises, and enterprises have to be restrained by the owner
and should not harm the owner's equity, he said.
</P>
<P>
China will adopt all kinds of possible means, including direct
financing, to replenish the capital funds of enterprises, and the
country will cultivate and develop a diversity of investors in
order to push the separation of administrative functions from
enterprise management and change the way enterprises operate, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that China will also combine the reform of
state-owned enterprises with their reorganization, upgrading and
better management.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
