<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin on Economic Restructuring and Development Strategy (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Aiming at improving the state sector of the economy as a whole,
China will effectuate a strategic reorganization of state-owned
enterprises by managing well large enterprises while adopting a
flexible policy toward small ones.
</P>
<P>
By using capital as the bonds and relying on the market forces,
China will establish highly competitive large enterprise groups
with trans-regional, inter-trade, cross-ownership and
trans-national operations. China will also quicken the pace in
relaxing the control over small state-owned enterprises and
invigorating them by way of reorganization, association, merger,
leasing, contract operation, joint stock partnership or sell-off,
the top Party official said.
</P>
<P>
"We should encourage merger of enterprises, standardize
bankruptcy procedures, divert laid-off workers, increase
efficiency by downsizing staff and encourage reemployment projects
so as to form a competitive mechanism selecting the superior and
eliminating the inferior," he said.
</P>
<P>
On improving the structure and mode of distribution, Jiang said
China will combine remuneration according to work and remuneration
according to factors of production put in and by giving priority
to efficiency with due consideration to equity.
</P>
<P>
"We shall protect lawful incomes according to law, allowing and
encouraging part of the people to get wealthy first through honest
labor and lawful operations, and allowing and encouraging the use
of capital, technology and other factors of production to
participate in the distribution of gains," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang emphasized that all illegal earnings shall be banned and
China will take stock of irrational incomes and regulate the
excessively high incomes, improve the individual income tax
system, introduce such new taxes as inheritance tax, and
standardize income distribution so as to make income gaps more
reasonable and prevent polarization.
</P>
<P>
On coordinated growth of the regional economies, Jiang said the
state will increase its support for the central and western parts
by giving them priority in planning infrastructure and resources
development projects, instituting step by step a standard payment
transfer system, and encouraging both Chinese and overseas
investors to invest in the regions. It is necessary to further
develop all forms of association and cooperation between the
eastern and the central and western parts. "We shall pay more
attention and give active support to areas inhabited by ethnic
minorities in their economic development. We must try all possible
ways to minimize the regional development disparities step by
step," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Jiang emphasized that opening to the outside world is a
long-term basic state policy.
</P>
<P>
Confronted with the globalization trend in the economic,
scientific and technological development, China will take an even
more active stance in the world by improving the pattern of
opening up in all directions, at all levels and in a wide range,
developing an open economy, enhancing our international
competitiveness, optimizing our economic structure and improving
the quality of its national economy.
</P>
<P>
China will further lower the general level of tariffs and
encourage the import of advanced technologies and key equipment.
</P>
<P>
"We shall use foreign capital actively, rationally and
effectively. We shall open the service trade step by step. In
accordance with the law, we shall protect the rights and interests
of foreign-funded enterprises, grant them the same treatment as
their Chinese counterparts and improve guidance to and regulation
of these enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"We shall encourage Chinese investors to invest abroad in areas
that can bring China's comparative advantages into play so as to
make better use of both Chinese and foreign markets and resources.
We shall improve and enforce laws and statutes governing China's
trade and economic relations with foreign countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang told the congress that China will better operate the
special economic zones and the Pudong New Area in Shanghai,
encouraging them to continue to march in the forefront by playing
their demonstrative, diffusive and leading roles in making
institutional creations, upgrading industries and opening wider to
the outside world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
