<HEADLINE> Ningbo Imports 100 Million Tons of Iron Ore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, September 12 (Xinhua) -- Beilun Port in Ningbo, east
China's Zhejiang Province, has handled over 100 million tons of
imported iron ore since entering operations in 1985.
</P>
<P>
The port's iron ore transshipping wharf for ships of 100,000
DWT began handling imported iron ore for the Shanghai Baogang Iron
And Steel Complex in 1985.
</P>
<P>
The volume of imported ore handled by the port has increased at
an annual rate of 18 percent since 1985, with Beilun currently
servicing 22 iron and steel corporations.
</P>
<P>
The port's iron ore storage capacity has increased from 500,000
tons to 2.35 million tons, and it set a new record in July by
unloading 5,000 tons of iron ore per hour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
