<HEADLINE> Italian Prime Minister's Office Damaged by Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The office of Italian Prime
Minister Romano Prodi was severely damaged by a fire that
accidentally broke out early today, the ANSA news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out on the first floor of the building around
1:30 a.m. local time and the prime minister's office sustained
damaged before the fire was brought under control, the news agency
said.
</P>
<P>
Prodi was away from Rome at the time, attending a meeting in
central-north city of Bologna with Spanish Prime Minister Jose
Maria Aznar.
</P>
<P>
The fire damaged home appliances, furniture, documents and some
precious paintings, ANSA said.
</P>
<P>
Initial results of an investigation revealed that the fire
might have been caused by a short-circuit, according to the news
agency. 
</P>
