<HEADLINE> 15th CPC National Congress Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 12 (Xinhua) -- The Communist Party of China
(CPC) opened its 15th national congress at the Great Hall of the
People here this morning. CPC Central Committee General Secretary
Jiang Zemin delivered a report to the congress on behalf of the
14th CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The 30,000-word report, which contains 10 parts, is entitled
"Hold High the Great Banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory for an
All-Round Advancement of the Cause of Building Socialism with
Chinese Characteristics to the 21st Century."
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the current congress is "an extremely important
congress." Held at the turn of the century to break new ground for
the future, it will ensure that "the whole Party will carry out
Comrade Deng Xiaoping's behests and march unswervingly and
triumphantly along the correct line adopted since the Third
Plenary Session of the Eleventh Central Committee."
</P>
<P>
He said "the theme of the congress is to hold high the great
banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory for an all-round advancement of the
cause of building socialism with Chinese characteristics to the
21st century."
</P>
<P>
Today's session, which began at 9:00 a.m., was presided over by
Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 delegates and specially invited delegates are
attending the congress. The CPC holds its national congress every
five years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
