<HEADLINE> Czech Republic's Grain Output to Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The total grain output of the
Czech Republic will reach 6.92 million tons this year, up 7.1
percent from last year, according to the figures released by the
National Statistics Bureau here today.
</P>
<P>
This will be the best harvest in the Czech Republic in recent
years despite the most serious floods recorded in the century.
</P>
<P>
The country has spent more money on the grain production this
year and the sown area of crops increased by 7.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Czech Republic's grain output this year will meet the
needs of its people and the country will have a surplus of
200,000 tons of grain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
