<HEADLINE> Tung: HK Developing Steadily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 11 (Xinhua) -- The Chief Executive of
China's Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), Tung
Chee-hwa, said here today that Hong Kong has been developing
steadily since it returned to the embrace of motherland on July 1.
</P>
<P>
Tung, who flew in New York last night, told a luncheon
participated by representatives of local economic, trade and
financial circles that Hong Kong has withstood recent turbulence
in other Southeast Asian financial markets, showing its finances
and fiscal policy are solid.
</P>
<P>
"The fundamentals in Hong Kong remain extremely strong for the
future," said Tung at the luncheon feted by the Asian Society in
cooperation with The Hong Kong Economic &AMP; Trade Office, The Hong
Kong Association of New York, and The National Committee of
U.S.-China Relations.
</P>
<P>
"We expect GDP growth this year to be around 5.5 percent.
Inflation continues to decline, albeit slowly," the chief
executive said.
</P>
<P>
Tung predicted that with Hong Kong's new airport opening next
year, SAR's quality as an aviation and service hub will "greatly"
improved.
</P>
<P>
"We are following it up with a massive program of rail and
other infrastructure development to further improve our
efficiency and productivity," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
