<HEADLINE> Bank of Montreal Board of Directors to Meet in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TORONTO, September 11 (Xinhua) -- Bank of Montreal, the third
largest commercial bank in Canada, said today that its board of
directors will meet in Beijing on September 29.
</P>
<P>
"This will be the first time, in 180 years, that our board has
met outside the North American continent," said Matthew W.
Barrett, the bank's chairman and chief executive officer.
</P>
<P>
Barrett said that the board meeting in Beijing represents the
bank's strategic interest in China.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing meeting comes at a time "when the ties between
Canada and China are broader and stronger than they have ever been
before," Barrett told the Canada-China Business Council and the
Hong Kong-Canada Business Association luncheon here today.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the meeting coincides the official opening of its
branch in Beijing, Barrett noted.
</P>
<P>
The branch makes Bank of Montreal "the first Canadian bank, the
third North American bank and the eighth foreign bank to open a
full branch in the Chinese capital," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Bank of Montreal Group of Companies is one of the largest
financial institutions in North America, with 140 billion U.S.
dollars in assets and more than 1,100 branches in Canada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
