<HEADLINE> Annan Ready to Mediate Civil War in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 11 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan said today he was ready to mediate the civil war in
Algeria if the door was open.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters, Annan said:"Right from the beginning, as
Secretary-General of the United States, I said I would offer my
mediation whenever I think that would be helpful."
</P>
<P>
"No one can fight with me for defending the security of life
and the fundamental rights of individuals," the U.N. chief added.
</P>
<P>
He did not say whether he had already offered his mediation
services.
</P>
<P>
Algeria plunged into violence after the authorities in 1992
canceled the general election. About 60,000 people have since
died. 
</P>
